node.text: The math doesn't work. We only control the airfield in Kabul. Why are there only 1300 on flights? Get them out of Afghanistan and get them somewhere else, Guam, anywhere if it's about processing. It's not just a processing issue in all cases, refugees can't all get to the airports. According to the LA Times, the Taliban is already beating people in crowds at check points around it. What happens to Americans who might be stuck trying to get out after the 31st? The White House was evasive on that question earlier. Lawmakers should be focused on making this right, the threat to the people who helped America is a very scary aspect of this exit.
